\title{Cartesian product of two sets}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-09}
\taxon{definition}
\meta{source}{[[paul-r-halmos]] [[halmos-1974-naive]] Ch.6}
\MML{zfmisc_1}{def 2}{K2}

\p{Let #{X} and #{Y} be sets. We define their \define{Cartesian product} to be the set #{X\times Y} such that for all objects #{z}, we have #{z\in X\times Y} if and only if there exists objects #{x} and #{y} such that #{x\in X} and #{y\in Y} and #{z=(x,y)}.}